      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MACHO ARQUERO (1) looks the one to beat in the opener on the back of his recent efforts at York and Pinjarra. He bumped into a big winner there last start, but was in the market and was best of the rest behind the winner. Maps to get every chance again and looks set to knock over his maiden. MR FRODO (3) comes through the same race where he finished 4L behind Macho Aquero last time out at Pinjarra. A better barrier this time helps and the extra furlong doesn't look an issue. Can feature in the finish bringing in the stronger formlines. SISTER MARY (7) gets out to this trip now  and looks ready to peak. She's a lightly-raced filly and the inside draw should see her get every chance. Wouldn't surprise to see her go to another level now. OVATHEBAR (4) is better than he showed last start and was sound here two back. Can bounce back. CROMBIE (2) is next best.",
